{
  "_doc": "Course 2 — KNOW YOUR NUMBERS (CPL & CPBJ). Locked doodle master style, multi-image explainer builds. Exact narration from booked-course2-narration.md, Torque Marshal. ~4 min.",
  "scenes": [
    {"id": "title", "text": "KNOW YOUR NUMBERS", "sub": "COURSE 2", "text_y": 110, "emph": "NUMBERS", "mood": "neutral",
     "vo": "Alright. Last course I told you a cheap lead that never books is the most expensive lead there is. Today I prove it.",
     "char": {"x": 400, "y": 470, "scale": 0.64, "hat": "hardhat", "tool": "wrench", "gesture_at": 6},
     "assets": [{"id": "calculator", "w": 240, "x": 1360, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.5, "sfx": "pop"}]},
    {"id": "gobroke", "text": "GOING BROKE — BUSY", "text_y": 120, "emph": "BROKE", "mood": "frustrated",
     "vo": "Because here's how good contractors quietly go broke. They chase the cheapest leads they can find, never run the math, and wonder why the busier they get, the less money is left at the end of the month.",
     "char": {"x": 320, "y": 460, "scale": 0.6, "hat": "hardhat", "tool": "wrench"},
     "assets": [{"id": "coin", "w": 200, "x": 980, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.5, "mark": "x", "label": "CHEAP LEADS"},
                {"id": "dollarstack", "w": 280, "x": 1440, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 3.0, "mark": "x", "sfx": "pop", "label": "PROFIT GONE"}]},
    {"id": "twofix", "text": "JUST TWO NUMBERS", "text_y": 120, "emph": "TWO",
     "vo": "The fix is two numbers. Just two. Learn these, and nobody ever talks you into a bad deal again.",
     "assets": [{"id": "leadhand", "w": 260, "x": 640, "y": 620, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "CPL"},
                {"id": "calendar", "w": 300, "x": 1280, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 2.2, "sfx": "ding", "label": "CPBJ"}]},
    {"id": "cpl", "text": "CPL = COST PER LEAD", "text_y": 120, "emph": "CPL",
     "transition_in": "blur", "transition_text": "NUMBER ONE...",
     "vo": "Number one. Cost per lead. C P L. Dead simple. It's what you pay to get one person to raise their hand and say, hey, I might hire you.",
     "assets": [{"id": "moneybag", "w": 280, "x": 600, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "YOU PAY"},
                {"id": "leadhand", "w": 240, "x": 1340, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 3.2, "sfx": "pop", "label": "ONE LEAD"}]},
    {"id": "cplformula", "text": "SPEND ÷ LEADS", "text_y": 120, "emph": "÷",
     "vo": "You spend a thousand bucks on ads and twenty people call? That's fifty bucks a lead. Total spend, divided by leads. That's the whole formula. Most guys stop right here, see a low number, and feel like a genius. Don't.",
     "assets": [{"id": "moneybag", "w": 220, "x": 480, "y": 620, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "$1,000"},
                {"id": "leadhand", "w": 200, "x": 960, "y": 620, "anim": "popIn", "t": 2.6, "sfx": "pop", "label": "20 LEADS"},
                {"id": "coin", "w": 200, "x": 1440, "y": 620, "anim": "popIn", "t": 4.6, "sfx": "ding", "label": "$50 EACH"}]},
    {"id": "cpbj", "text": "CPBJ = COST PER BOOKED JOB", "text_y": 110, "emph": "CPBJ",
     "transition_in": "blur", "transition_text": "NUMBER TWO...",
     "vo": "Because number two is the one that actually matters. Cost per booked job. C P B J. Not what you paid for a phone call. What you paid for a job that actually pays you.",
     "assets": [{"id": "phonemap", "w": 280, "x": 620, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "mark": "x", "label": "A CALL"},
                {"id": "calendar", "w": 360, "x": 1340, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 4.0, "mark": "check", "sfx": "ding", "label": "A PAID JOB"}]},
    {"id": "maybemoney", "text": "LEAD = MAYBE · JOB = MONEY", "text_y": 110, "emph": "MONEY",
     "vo": "A lead is a maybe. A booked job is money in the bank. And the gap between those two numbers is exactly where your profit lives or dies.",
     "assets": [{"id": "leadhand", "w": 220, "x": 540, "y": 620, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "MAYBE"},
                {"id": "scale", "w": 300, "x": 980, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 2.6, "sfx": "pop"},
                {"id": "dollarstack", "w": 260, "x": 1440, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 3.6, "sfx": "ding", "label": "MONEY"}]},
    {"id": "runmath", "text": "RUN THE MATH", "text_y": 120, "emph": "MATH",
     "transition_in": "blur", "transition_text": "RUN THE MATH...",
     "vo": "Let's run it. You spend a thousand dollars. You get twenty leads. Fifty bucks a lead. Looking good.",
     "assets": [{"id": "moneybag", "w": 220, "x": 460, "y": 620, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "$1,000"},
                {"id": "leadhand", "w": 190, "x": 940, "y": 620, "anim": "popIn", "t": 1.8, "sfx": "pop", "label": "20 LEADS"},
                {"id": "coin", "w": 190, "x": 1420, "y": 620, "anim": "popIn", "t": 3.2, "sfx": "ding", "label": "$50 / LEAD"}]},
    {"id": "fourbook", "text": "ONLY 4 BOOK", "text_y": 120, "emph": "4",
     "vo": "But only four of them book. So that same thousand dollars bought you four jobs. That's two hundred and fifty dollars a job.",
     "assets": [{"id": "calendar", "w": 360, "x": 660, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "mark": "check", "label": "4 JOBS"},
                {"id": "dollarstack", "w": 280, "x": 1360, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 3.0, "sfx": "ding", "label": "$250 EACH"}]},
    {"id": "realcost", "text": "$50 vs $250", "text_y": 120, "emph": "$250",
     "vo": "Your cost per lead said fifty. Your real cost, the one that actually hits your bank account, is two hundred and fifty. Five times higher. That's the number nobody puts on the invoice.",
     "assets": [{"id": "coin", "w": 200, "x": 560, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "CPL $50"},
                {"id": "scale", "w": 280, "x": 980, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 2.4, "sfx": "pop"},
                {"id": "dollarstack", "w": 320, "x": 1440, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 4.0, "sfx": "ding", "label": "CPBJ $250"}]},
    {"id": "closeslip", "text": "CLOSE RATE SLIPS", "text_y": 120, "emph": "SLIPS",
     "transition_in": "blur", "transition_text": "NOW WATCH...",
     "vo": "Now watch what happens when your close rate slips. Same thousand dollars. Same fifty-dollar leads. But this time, only two book instead of four.",
     "assets": [{"id": "leadhand", "w": 220, "x": 600, "y": 620, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "20 LEADS"},
                {"id": "calendar", "w": 340, "x": 1340, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 4.0, "mark": "x", "sfx": "buzz", "label": "ONLY 2"}]},
    {"id": "doubles", "text": "CPBJ DOUBLES → $500", "text_y": 110, "emph": "$500", "wash": "yellow",
     "vo": "Your cost per lead didn't move an inch. Still fifty. But your cost per booked job just doubled, to five hundred. Same ads, same spend, half the money.",
     "assets": [{"id": "coin", "w": 200, "x": 520, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "STILL $50"},
                {"id": "scale", "w": 300, "x": 960, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 2.2, "sfx": "pop"},
                {"id": "dollarstack", "w": 380, "x": 1460, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 3.6, "sfx": "buzz", "label": "$500 / JOB"}]},
    {"id": "theleak", "text": "THE LEAK IS THE CLOSE", "text_y": 120, "emph": "LEAK", "mood": "frustrated",
     "vo": "The leak was never the lead price. It was what happened after the phone rang.",
     "char": {"x": 320, "y": 460, "scale": 0.6, "hat": "hardhat"},
     "assets": [{"id": "phonemap", "w": 300, "x": 1280, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "AFTER THE CALL"}]},
    {"id": "cheaptrap", "text": "$15 SHARED LEAD", "text_y": 120, "emph": "SHARED",
     "transition_in": "blur", "transition_text": "CHEAP LEADS LIE...",
     "vo": "This is why cheap leads are a trap. A shared lead off some app for fifteen bucks sounds like a steal, until you find out four other guys got the same lead, half of them never answer, and maybe one in twenty turns into a job.",
     "assets": [{"id": "sharedlead", "w": 380, "x": 640, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "$15 — 4 GUYS"},
                {"id": "ghost", "w": 240, "x": 1380, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 5.0, "mark": "x", "sfx": "buzz", "label": "NEVER ANSWER"}]},
    {"id": "cheapmath", "text": "$15 LEAD = $300 JOB", "text_y": 120, "emph": "$300",
     "vo": "Do the math, and that fifteen-dollar lead cost you three hundred a job. Meanwhile the expensive, exclusive lead that books a third of the time is the cheapest one you've got.",
     "assets": [{"id": "coin", "w": 200, "x": 540, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "mark": "x", "label": "$15 LEAD"},
                {"id": "dollarstack", "w": 260, "x": 980, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 2.4, "sfx": "buzz", "label": "$300 JOB"},
                {"id": "handshake", "w": 280, "x": 1460, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 4.6, "mark": "check", "sfx": "ding", "label": "EXCLUSIVE WINS"}]},
    {"id": "cheapexp", "text": "CHEAP IS EXPENSIVE", "text_y": 120, "emph": "EXPENSIVE", "wash": "yellow",
     "vo": "Cheap is expensive. Judge every source by the booked job, never the lead.",
     "assets": [{"id": "coin", "w": 220, "x": 640, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "mark": "x", "label": "THE LEAD"},
                {"id": "calendar", "w": 340, "x": 1320, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 2.4, "mark": "check", "sfx": "ding", "label": "THE JOB"}]},
    {"id": "homework", "text": "PULL LAST MONTH", "text_y": 120, "emph": "LAST",
     "transition_in": "blur", "transition_text": "DO THIS NOW...",
     "vo": "Here's your homework, and it's the most valuable five minutes you'll spend this month. Pull up last month. What did you spend to get work. Ads, lead apps, all of it.",
     "assets": [{"id": "calculator", "w": 260, "x": 540, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4},
                {"id": "megaphone", "w": 240, "x": 980, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 3.2, "sfx": "pop", "label": "ADS"},
                {"id": "phonemap", "w": 240, "x": 1440, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 4.4, "sfx": "ping", "label": "LEAD APPS"}]},
    {"id": "divide", "text": "SPEND ÷ JOBS = TRUTH", "text_y": 115, "emph": "TRUTH",
     "vo": "Now count the jobs that actually came from it. Divide one by the other. That's your real cost per booked job.",
     "assets": [{"id": "dollarstack", "w": 240, "x": 500, "y": 620, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "SPEND"},
                {"id": "calendar", "w": 280, "x": 960, "y": 620, "anim": "popIn", "t": 2.0, "sfx": "ding", "label": "JOBS"},
                {"id": "calculator", "w": 220, "x": 1440, "y": 620, "anim": "popIn", "t": 3.4, "sfx": "pop", "label": "= TRUTH"}]},
    {"id": "doitonce", "text": "DO IT ONCE", "text_y": 120, "emph": "ONCE", "mood": "delighted",
     "vo": "Most owners have never done this once in their entire lives. Do it one time, and you will never look at a marketing bill the same way again.",
     "char": {"x": 360, "y": 440, "scale": 0.64, "hat": "hardhat", "tool": "wrench", "gesture_at": 2},
     "assets": [{"id": "clipboard", "w": 360, "x": 1320, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "sfx": "pop"}]},
    {"id": "baitmeal", "text": "BAIT vs MEAL", "text_y": 120, "emph": "MEAL",
     "transition_in": "blur", "transition_text": "TWO NUMBERS...",
     "vo": "That's the whole lesson. Two numbers. Cost per lead is the bait. Cost per booked job is the meal.",
     "assets": [{"id": "leadhand", "w": 240, "x": 600, "y": 620, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "label": "CPL = BAIT"},
                {"id": "dollarstack", "w": 300, "x": 1340, "y": 600, "anim": "popIn", "t": 2.6, "sfx": "ding", "label": "CPBJ = MEAL"}]},
    {"id": "storytruth", "text": "STORY vs TRUTH", "text_y": 120, "emph": "TRUTH", "mood": "neutral",
     "vo": "One tells you a story. The other tells you the truth. And now you know which is which.",
     "char": {"x": 340, "y": 460, "scale": 0.6, "hat": "hardhat", "tool": "wrench", "gesture_at": 0},
     "assets": [{"id": "scale", "w": 360, "x": 1300, "y": 600, "anim": "drawOn", "t": 0.4, "sfx": "pop"}]},
